{"title": "In Their Choice of Guests, Trump and Congressional Democrats Sent Dueling Messages", "url": "https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2017/02/28/us/politics/in-their-choice-of-guests-trump-and-congressional-democrats-sent-dueling-messages.html?mcubz=0", "text": "Doug Mills/The New York Times\n\nFour of Mr. Trump\u2019s guests are family members of people who, authorities said, were killed by immigrants living in the United States illegally.\n\nStephen Crowley/The New York Times\n\nSusan Oliver, standing next to her daughter Jenna, and Jessica Davis, are widows of two California police officers who were killed in 2014.\n\nDoug Mills/The New York Times\n\nJamiel Shaw, Sr., whose son was killed in 2008, appeared in an ad for Mr. Trump and gave a speech at the Republican National Convention. His son was a high school football star in Los Angeles and was 17 at the time of his death.\n\nDoug Mills/The New York Times\n\nDenisha Merriweather graduated from a private high school and college, benefiting from a school-choice program in Florida. Betsy DeVos, Mr. Trump\u2019s education secretary, supports expanding similar voucher programs.\n\nDoug Mills/The New York Times\n\nMegan Crowley is a student at Notre Dame who has a rare genetic disorder known as Pompe disease. The disease prompted her father, John Crowley, to start a pharmaceutical company to search for a cure.\n\nDoug Mills/The New York Times\n\nJessica Gregory is an 18-year-old Maryland honor student who at birth was found to have spina bifida and has had 11 operations at Children\u2019s National Health System. She was joined by her mother, Shelia Gregory.\n\nDoug Mills/The New York Times\n\nMaureen McCarthy Scalia, the widow of the late Justice Antonin Scalia, was also seated with the first lady. At the end of January, Mr. Trump named Judge Neil M. Gorsuch to fill the Supreme Court vacancy left by Justice Scalia. Hearings on Judge Gorsuch\u2019s nomination will begin next month.\n\nDoug Mills/The New York Times\n\nCarryn Owens is the widow of Chief Petty Officer William Owens, a commando killed in a Special Operations raid in Yemen last month. Ms. Owens received the longest applause of the evening after Mr. Trump recognized her in the speech.\n\nGuests of Congress\n\nIn a form of protest, Democrats in Congress invited their own guests, many of whom have been or could be affected by the Trump administration\u2019s policies. A handful of congressional Republicans also announced guests, though they were less politically charged. Some key issues represented:", "publish_date": "2017-02-28", "authors": "Larry Buchanan and Alicia Parlapiano", "type": "article"}